respect.

the name: however, it only grinned a little wider.

she went on. `Would you tell me, please, which way
I ought to go from here?'                   
                                            
`That depends a good deal on where you want to
get to,' said the Cat.
                                            
`I don't much care where--' said Alice.
                                            
`Then it doesn't matter which way you go,'
said the Cat.
                                            
`--so long as I get SOMEWHERE,' Alice added
as an explanation.
                                            
`Oh, you're sure to do that,' said the Cat,
`if you only walk long enough.'

entities.name: yank-movement
message: Trying to destroy bugs by using yank
and without knowing how yank moves
After a character-wise yank, the cursor
is moved to the first yanked character
that is closest to the start of the buffer.
With a line-wise yank command the
cursor is put in the first line, but the
column is unmodified, thus it may not
be on the first yanked character.
